Problem_with_redundant_assumption:
Assumption:
Assumption 1: $n$ is a positive integer.
Assumption 2: $$ \sqrt{n+1}-\sqrt{n}
 = \frac{(\sqrt{n+1}-\sqrt{n})(\sqrt{n+1}+\sqrt{n})}{\sqrt{n+1}+\sqrt{n}}
 = \frac{1}{\sqrt{n+1}+\sqrt{n}}
 < \frac{1}{2\sqrt{n}}
$$
Problem: 
Prove that $$\lim_{n\to\infty}\left( \sqrt{n+1} - \sqrt{n} \right) = 0.$$
